The **European Union (EU)** is a political and economic union of European countries that work together to promote integration, peace, and prosperity. It is one of the most influential regional organizations in the world.

## Origins and History

- **1951** – European Coal and Steel Community (ECSC) founded by six countries (Belgium, France, Italy, Luxembourg, Netherlands, West Germany).  
- **1957** – Treaty of Rome established the European Economic Community (EEC).  
- **1993** – Maastricht Treaty formally created the European Union.  
- **2009** – Lisbon Treaty reformed EU institutions and strengthened integration.  

## Membership

- Currently **27 member states** (after the United Kingdom left in 2020, known as Brexit).  
- Enlargement has included countries from Western, Northern, Southern, and Eastern Europe.  
- Membership requires meeting democratic, economic, and legal standards (Copenhagen Criteria
